sentences.english: They have short, stubby tails and long, sharp fangs.
sentences.chinese: 他们有短粗的尾巴和长而尖利的犬齿。

sentences.english: It has a pair of large canine teeth in its upper jaw.
sentences.chinese: 在它的上颚有一对大的犬齿。

sentences.english: Especially large, sharp canine characterizes the carnivorous animals.
sentences.chinese: 大而尖利的犬齿是食肉动物的特征。

sentences.english: Management involved positioning the canine teeth into the central incisor region and placing porcelain veneers on these teeth.
sentences.chinese: 管理参与定位犬齿到区域中切牙瓷贴面，把这些牙齿。

sentences.english: The hepatic fissures may be curved like the waves or even the canine teeth overlapping.
sentences.chinese: 肝裂可能是弯曲的，呈波浪形甚至犬齿交错状。

sentences.english: Indonesian wild pig with enormous curved canine teeth.
sentences.chinese: 猪，雄性有巨大弯曲的犬齿。

sentences.english: Those who were vampires were thought to have longer than usual eye teeth.
sentences.chinese: 人们通常认为吸血鬼的上犬齿比常人要长。

sentences.english: The carnivorous animals are characterized especially by large, sharp canine teeth.
sentences.chinese: 肉食动物的特征是大而尖的犬齿。

definition: premolar tooth (immediately behind canine teeth in some mammals)
(of uneven surfaces) to fit together/(of gear wheels) to mesh/(dentistry) occlusion/bite
